headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored 25 points and the Brooklyn Nets withstood a late rally and another triple-double by Nikola Jokic to beat the Denver Nuggets 122-120 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Nets withstand Jokic's triple-double, beat Nuggets

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had 28 points, Donovan Mitchell added 23 and the Cleveland Cavaliers overcame a 16-point second-half deficit to beat the Charlotte Hornets 114-108 on Sunday for their fourth win in the last five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland, Cavaliers battle back from 16 down to beat Hornets

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 34 points, James Harden had 18 points and 14 assists and the Philadelphia 76ers cruised to a wire-to-wire 112-93 win over the fading Washington Wizards on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Harden help 76ers cruise past Wizards 112-93

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Pelicans second-year pro Trey Murphy III was only beginning to earn regular minutes off the bench as a rookie last spring.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murphy hits 9 3s, scores 41, Pelicans down Blazers 127-110

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jalen Williams scored 21 points and had 10 assists, and Oklahoma City used a balanced effort on offense without Shai Gilgeous-Alexander to beat the San Antonio Spurs 102-90 on Sunday night as they compete for a berth in the Western Conference...
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams lifts Thunder past Spurs and into West's 10th seed

events.name: New York Knicks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 33 points in a bounce-back performance, RJ Barrett got 20 of his 30 in the second half, and the New York Knicks snapped their three-game losing streak with a 112-108 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Knicks hold off Lakers 112-108 to snap 3-game skid
